(Packaging and Runtime Snapshot \(Alpha\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Last refresh: 2026-04-18) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This guide describes the production packaging workflow for Atho alpha builds. The packaging) Tj
T*
(process keeps repository-relative paths intact, captures a timestamped snapshot, and supports) Tj
T*
(reproducible release verification with checksums and signatures.) Tj
T*
(- Packaging Goal) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The current packaging strategy is intentionally conservative:) Tj
T*
(- preserve runnable repository structure,) Tj
T*
(- avoid breaking path assumptions used by runtime modules,) Tj
T*
(- make release artifacts portable across operators,) Tj
T*
(- keep a deterministic, timestamped build trail.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is preferred over aggressive single-binary packaging until all runtime paths are fully) Tj
T*
(migrated to OS-native application data directories.) Tj
T*
